blocks.name: sltsolem1
blocks.content: Lemma for ~ sltso . The sign expansion relationship totally orders the surreal signs. (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 8-Jun-2011.)

blocks.name: sltso
blocks.content: Surreal less than totally orders the surreals. Alling's axiom (O). (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 9-Jun-2011.)
blocks.origin:
thm sltso() {
  |- wor(cslt, csur)
} = {
  soseq(hs2, hs0, hs3, hs1, cslt, csur, ctp(cop(c1o, emptycls), cop(c1o, c2o), cop(emptycls, c2o)), cpr(c1o, c2o))
  sltsolem1()
  df-no(hs2, hs0)
  df-slt(hs2, hs3, hs0, hs1)
  nosgnn0()
  diff.hs2.s(hs0)
  diff.hs2.s(hs3)
  diff.hs2.s(hs1)
  diff.hs0.s(hs3)
  diff.hs0.s(hs1)
  diff.hs3.s(hs1)
  diff.hs2.c(csur)
  diff.hs2.c(ctp(cop(c1o, emptycls), cop(c1o, c2o), cop(emptycls, c2o)))
  diff.hs2.c(cpr(c1o, c2o))
  diff.hs0.c(csur)
  diff.hs0.c(ctp(cop(c1o, emptycls), cop(c1o, c2o), cop(emptycls, c2o)))
  diff.hs0.c(cpr(c1o, c2o))
  diff.hs3.c(csur)
  diff.hs3.c(ctp(cop(c1o, emptycls), cop(c1o, c2o), cop(emptycls, c2o)))
  diff.hs1.c(cpr(c1o, c2o))
  diff.hs3.s(hs0)
}
